"{\"uid\": \"en.tempo.co-read-1901871-todays-top-3-news-indonesia-climbs-to-28th-in-paris-olympics-medal-standings\", \"text\": \"Translator  Tempo.co  Editor  Laila Afifa  August 9, 2024 | 04:35 pm  TEMPO.CO,Jakarta-Tempo Englishcompiled the top three news on Friday, August 9, 2024. Here are the highlights: Indonesia Climbs to 28th in Paris Olympics Medal Standings, Jokowi to Attend Environmental 'LIKE Festival' in Jakarta, and \\u00a0Indonesian Immigration Detains 2 Suspects of Human Smuggling to Australia.  The following is the list of the top 3 news onTempo Englishtoday:  1. Indonesia Climbs to 28th in Paris Olympics Medal Standings  TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - Indonesia's medal count has risen to two golds and one bronze, bringing the nation to the 28th position in the \\u00a02024 Paris Olympics standings. The latest gold was clinched by weightlifter Rizki Juniansyah in the men's 73-kg category.  According to the Olympics' official site, as of 4:00 a.m. Indonesian Western Time (WIB) on Friday, August 9, the United States continued to dominate the medal tally with 30 gold, 38 silver, and 35 bronze medals.  Click here to read more  2. Jokowi to Attend Environmental 'LIKE Festival' in Jakarta  TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - President Joko Widodo or Jokowi will attend an environmental festival dubbed the LIKE (Lingkungan or environment, Iklim or climate, Kehutanan or forestry, and Energi Terbarukan or renewable energy) Festival at Jakarta Convention Center, Central Jakarta, on Friday, August 9, 2024. Yusuf Permana, the Presidential Secretariat Deputy for Protocol and Media confirmed in a written statement.  The first LIKE Festival last year was held as part of the preparations for the UN Framework Convention on Climate Change or the 28th Conference of the Parties or COP28 in Dubai. This year, COP29 will be held in Baku, Azerbaijan in November.  Click here to read more  3. Indonesian Immigration Detains 2 Suspects of Human Smuggling to Australia  TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - The Directorate General of Immigration arrested two people suspected of being involved in human smuggling to Australia. The two, Indonesian citizens with the initials DH and MA, were immediately detained and named as suspects.  Immigration is also investigating the involvement of an Italian citizen, GA, Meanwhile, DH and MA are being held at the Class I State Detention Center in Central Jakarta. They are charged with Article 120 of Immigration Law with a maximum of 15 years in prison and a Rp1.5 billion fine.  Click here to read more  Tempo.co  Recommended  World Cup 2026 Draw: Trump, Infantino and a Peace Prize  3 hours ago  10 Best World Cup Finals: The Most Memorable Matches in Football History  6 hours ago  Indonesia U-23 SEA Games 2025 Schedule: Philippines Await in Opener  1 days ago  Top 10 Best Football Managers in Europe in 25/26 Season  2 days ago  10 Oldest Players in World Cup History  3 days ago  2025 Thailand SEA Games Update: 11 Sports Venues Moved Due to Floods  4 days ago  Indonesia Unveils U-23 SEA Games Squad Featuring Four Diaspora Players  4 days ago  Flooding Forces Thailand to Move 10 SEA Games Sports to Bangkok  5 days ago  Indonesia Forward Hokky Caraka Aims to Settle Personal 'Debt' at SEA Games 2025  5 days ago  U-23 Indonesia Team Departs for Thailand on Friday for 2025 SEA Games  5 days ago  Today's Top 3 News: Prabowo Departs for Sumatra, 10 Best Places to Retire in US 2026  7 jam lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News: Prabowo Departs for Sumatra to Inspect Disaster-Hit Areas  1 hari lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News: 10 Best Places to Retire in US 2026, Affordable and Peaceful  2 hari lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News: Prabowo Says Monitoring Sumatra Floods, Customer Reports Mirae Asset Sekuritas  3 hari lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News:  M6.3 Megathrust E